<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office"
xmlns:w="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word"
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<style>
body { font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; margin: 1in; color: #1a1a1a; }
h1 { font-size: 22pt; color: #0078D4; border-bottom: 2px solid #0078D4; padding-bottom: 6pt; }
h2 { font-size: 16pt; color: #0078D4; margin-top: 24pt; }
h3 { font-size: 13pt; color: #333; margin-top: 18pt; }
blockquote { background: #f0f6ff; border-left: 4px solid #0078D4; padding: 10pt 14pt; margin: 12pt 0; font-style: italic; }
code, pre { font-family: Consolas, monospace; font-size: 10.5pt; }
pre { background: #f5f5f5; border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 10pt 14pt; margin: 10pt 0; white-space: pre-wrap; }
table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 12pt 0; }
th { background: #0078D4; color: white; padding: 8pt 12pt; text-align: left; font-weight: bold; }
td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8pt 12pt; }
tr:nth-child(even) { background: #f9f9f9; }
.label { display: inline-block; background: #e8f0fe; color: #0078D4; padding: 2pt 8pt; border-radius: 3pt; font-weight: bold; font-size: 9pt; margin-bottom: 4pt; }
.talking-point { background: #fff8e1; border-left: 4px solid #f9a825; padding: 8pt 14pt; margin: 8pt 0; font-style: italic; }
.checklist { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; }
.checklist li { padding: 4pt 0; }
.checklist li:before { content: "☐ "; font-size: 12pt; }
hr { border: none; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; margin: 20pt 0; }
</style>
<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml><w:WordDocument><w:View>Print</w:View></w:WordDocument></xml><![endif]-->
</head>
<body>

<h1>Copilot Cowork Demo Script</h1>

<table>
<tr><td><b>Demo week</b></td><td>April 27 &#8211; May 1, 2026</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Persona</b></td><td>James Bowen, VP of Operations, Apex Manufacturing</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Interface</b></td><td>Microsoft 365 Copilot Chat (Cowork) &#8212; single UI, all prompts</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Setup</b></td><td>Run <code>.\Load-DemoData.ps1</code> before the demo</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>Scene-Setting (30 seconds)</h2>

<blockquote>
&#8220;It&#8217;s Monday morning. I&#8217;m VP of Operations at Apex Manufacturing. I&#8217;ve been out of office and I&#8217;m catching up on a busy week ahead &#8212; we&#8217;ve got a major customer meeting with Adatum Corp on Thursday and a product launch to plan for ProLine X. Let me show you how I use Copilot to get up to speed, prep, and get work done &#8212; all from one place.&#8221;
</blockquote>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 1: Catch Me Up</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>Catch me up on what's been happening this week. What are the key things 
I need to know from my emails, chats, and files?</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Spencer&#8217;s Adatum meeting request + deal financials ($2.4M)</li>
<li>Renee&#8217;s competitive analysis (Fabrikam vs. Northwind vs. us)</li>
<li>David&#8217;s prior meeting notes from January 15</li>
<li>Molly&#8217;s ProLine X launch announcement (GA June 9)</li>
<li>Teams chat threads about the briefing deck and launch plan</li>
<li>OneDrive files (briefing deck draft, battle card, exec summary)</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;One prompt, and Copilot searched across my emails, chats, calendar, and files. I instantly know I have a $2.4M deal meeting Thursday and a product launch to plan &#8212; no app switching.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 2: Deep Dive on the Deal</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>Tell me everything I know about the Adatum Corp deal. Include the opportunity 
details, key contacts, deal financials, competitive landscape, and any recent 
news. Pull from my emails, files, and CRM.</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>

<table>
<tr><th>Data Point</th><th>Detail</th><th>Source</th></tr>
<tr><td>Opportunity</td><td>ProLine X Platform Deployment &#8212; $2.4M, Propose stage, 65% probability</td><td>Dynamics 365</td></tr>
<tr><td>Key Contact</td><td>Lisa Chen, VP of Procurement (decision maker)</td><td>CRM + David&#8217;s email</td></tr>
<tr><td>Key Contact</td><td>Marcus Webb, Director of Operations (tech evaluator)</td><td>CRM + David&#8217;s email</td></tr>
<tr><td>Deal Financials</td><td>$1.2M license + $480K implementation + $240K support + $480K IoT</td><td>Spencer&#8217;s email</td></tr>
<tr><td>Our Edge</td><td>8-week deployment (vs. Fabrikam&#8217;s 6 months), built-in AI/ML</td><td>Renee&#8217;s email</td></tr>
<tr><td>Proof Point</td><td>ProLine S delivered 18.3% throughput improvement (they asked for 15%)</td><td>Spencer&#8217;s chat + CRM notes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Market News</td><td>Adatum announced $50M smart manufacturing investment</td><td>Spencer&#8217;s email</td></tr>
<tr><td>Deadline</td><td>Must commit by end of Q2 (June 30) or budget rolls</td><td>David&#8217;s email + CRM notes</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;Copilot connected my emails, my colleague&#8217;s chats, AND the CRM record in Dynamics 365. I have the full deal picture &#8212; financials, contacts, competitive intel, and market context &#8212; without opening a single app.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 3: Meeting Prep</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>Help me prepare for my meeting with Adatum Corp on Thursday at 10 AM. 
Create a prep brief with: who's attending, what they care about, our key 
differentiators, risks to address, and recommended talking points.</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b> A structured prep brief pulling from:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Calendar:</b> Attendees &#8212; Spencer Low, Renee Lo, David So (internal); Lisa Chen, Marcus Webb (external)</li>
<li><b>Emails:</b> Customer priorities = speed to value + ROI; budget deadline June 30</li>
<li><b>CRM:</b> Opportunity stage, probability, prior meeting notes</li>
<li><b>Competitive intel:</b> Our 8-week deployment vs. Fabrikam&#8217;s 6 months; our AI/ML vs. Northwind&#8217;s legacy</li>
<li><b>Recommended talking points:</b> ProLine S success (18.3%), Azure IoT partnership, modular start-small approach</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;This prep brief would normally take me an hour to assemble &#8212; pulling from old meeting notes, emails from three colleagues, and the CRM. Copilot did it in seconds.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 4: Research the Customer</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>What do I know about Adatum Corp's recent strategic direction? Are there any 
news items, announcements, or intelligence from my team that I should be aware 
of before Thursday?</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>$50M smart manufacturing investment across North American plants</li>
<li>CTO pushing AI-first vendor selection</li>
<li>Q2 budget deadline (June 30) &#8212; commit now or wait another fiscal year</li>
<li>January 15 meeting notes showing high satisfaction with ProLine S</li>
<li>Company profile: $450M revenue, 3,200 employees, Redmond WA</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;I asked David to do customer research &#8212; turns out the intel was already scattered across my emails and CRM notes. Copilot found it all.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 5: Product Launch Status</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>What's the status of the ProLine X launch? Summarize what my team has shared 
about the timeline, product highlights, target accounts, and competitive 
positioning.</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>

<table>
<tr><th>Category</th><th>Details</th></tr>
<tr><td>GA Date</td><td>June 9, 2026 (from Molly Clark)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Product Highlights</td><td>40% faster processing, built-in AI/ML, Azure IoT native integration, modular design</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pipeline</td><td>$10M+ across 10 target accounts (from Spencer Low)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Top Accounts</td><td>Adatum Corp ($2.4M), Contoso Manufacturing ($1.8M), Tailspin Industries ($1.2M), Wide World Importers ($900K), Adventure Works ($850K), &#8230;</td></tr>
</table>

<p><b>Competitive comparison (from Renee Lo):</b></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Feature</th><th>Apex ProLine X</th><th>Fabrikam X200</th><th>Northwind NX-Pro</th></tr>
<tr><td>Processing Speed</td><td><b>40% faster</b></td><td>15% faster</td><td>Baseline</td></tr>
<tr><td>AI/ML Built-in</td><td><b>Yes</b></td><td>Add-on</td><td>No</td></tr>
<tr><td>IoT Integration</td><td><b>Azure native</b></td><td>AWS only</td><td>Custom</td></tr>
<tr><td>Deployment Time</td><td><b>8 weeks</b></td><td>6 months</td><td>4 months</td></tr>
<tr><td>Starting Price</td><td>$800K</td><td>$950K</td><td>$700K</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;Molly, Spencer, and Renee each sent me separate emails and chats about the launch. Copilot stitched them together into one coherent status update.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 6: Draft a Deliverable</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>Draft an executive summary for the ProLine X launch plan. Include the launch 
timeline, product highlights, target accounts and total pipeline value, 
competitive positioning, and key risks. This is for a board update.</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot creates:</b> A board-ready summary including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Launch objective + June 9 GA date (from Molly&#8217;s email)</li>
<li>Product highlights: 40% faster, AI/ML, Azure IoT, modular design</li>
<li>Top 10 target accounts with $10M+ pipeline (from Spencer&#8217;s email)</li>
<li>Competitive positioning table (from Renee&#8217;s email)</li>
<li>Risks: engineering delay, Fabrikam pricing counter-move, reference customer availability (from David&#8217;s email)</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;Molly needs this for the board deck by Friday. Instead of starting from a blank page, Copilot assembled it from the information my team already gave me. Real numbers, real context.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 7: Work with Office Documents</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>Look at the ProLine X Pipeline Tracker spreadsheet in my OneDrive. Which 
deals are in the Proposal or Negotiation stage? What's the total value 
of those deals and when are they expected to close?</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Opens and reads the .xlsx file from OneDrive</li>
<li>Identifies Adatum Corp ($2.4M, Proposal, Jun 30) and Adventure Works ($850K, Negotiation, Jun 15)</li>
<li>Calculates combined value: $3.25M expected to close by end of Q2</li>
<li>May reference related emails about these deals for additional context</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;Copilot can read Excel, Word, and PowerPoint files directly. I didn&#8217;t have to open the spreadsheet, find the right rows, and do the math myself. It understands the data.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 8: Summarize a Presentation</h2>
<p><span class="label">~1 MINUTE</span></p>

<pre>Summarize the Adatum Corp Briefing Deck in my OneDrive. What are the key 
points and what ROI are we projecting?</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Reads the .pptx file and summarizes all 10 slides</li>
<li>Highlights: 8-week implementation, $2.4M total Year 1 investment, 162% 3-year ROI, 14-month payback</li>
<li>References the reference customer quotes and proposed next steps</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;I can ask Copilot to summarize a deck without opening PowerPoint. Great for reviewing materials your team has prepared &#8212; especially when you&#8217;re short on time.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 9: Competitive Analysis</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>Based on the competitive analysis spreadsheet and Renee's emails, give me 
3 key talking points for why Adatum should choose us over Fabrikam and 
Northwind. Make them punchy - I need these for Thursday's meeting.</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Reads the ProLine X Competitive Analysis.xlsx &#8212; feature-by-feature comparison</li>
<li>Cross-references Renee&#8217;s competitive positioning emails</li>
<li>Generates 3 sharp talking points, e.g.:<br/>
    1. &#8220;We deploy in 8 weeks, Fabrikam takes 6 months &#8212; you&#8217;ll see ROI this fiscal year&#8221;<br/>
    2. &#8220;AI is included in our platform, not a $150K add-on&#8221;<br/>
    3. &#8220;Azure IoT native &#8212; since you&#8217;re already on Azure, integration is seamless&#8221;</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;Copilot combined the spreadsheet data with email context to create talking points that are specific to this customer. It knows Adatum is already on Azure from our team&#8217;s discussions.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 10: Escalation Triage</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>I have a lot going on this week. What are the most urgent items I need 
to respond to? Anything that needs my attention today or is time-sensitive?</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>
<ul>
<li><b>URGENT:</b> Fabrikam undercutting at Wide World Importers &#8212; Spencer needs response by Friday</li>
<li><b>AT RISK:</b> Engineering flagged IoT sensor issue (but later resolved)</li>
<li><b>ACTION NEEDED:</b> Board deck section due Friday 3 PM</li>
<li><b>REVIEW:</b> Press release draft needs review by Thursday EOD</li>
<li><b>APPROVE:</b> Launch event budget ($111.5K) and marketing contractor ($15K)</li>
<li>Unread emails from Spencer (Adventure Works signing), David (end-of-week summary)</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;With 26 emails, Teams chats, and channel messages all hitting my inbox, Copilot helps me prioritize. It identified the Fabrikam price cut as the most urgent item &#8212; that&#8217;s the one that could cost us a deal.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 11: Use a Custom Skill</h2>
<p><span class="label">~2 MINUTES</span></p>

<pre>Create a deal review brief for Adatum Corp.</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot does:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Activates the &#8220;Deal Review Brief&#8221; custom skill from OneDrive</li>
<li>Automatically gathers: emails, meeting notes, CRM data, Teams discussions, shared documents</li>
<li>Produces a polished Word document with account overview, relationship timeline, competitive landscape, action items, and recommended next steps</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;This is a custom skill I created for Copilot. It&#8217;s a reusable workflow &#8212; I just say &#8216;deal review brief&#8217; and it knows exactly what data to gather and how to format it. Think of skills as your personal playbooks.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Prompt 12: Channel Context</h2>
<p><span class="label">~1 MINUTE</span></p>

<pre>What's been discussed in the ProLine X Launch channel and the Adatum Deal 
Room this week? Any decisions or updates I should know about?</pre>

<p><b>What Copilot surfaces:</b></p>
<ul>
<li><b>ProLine X Launch:</b> Engineering issue flagged and resolved; GA confirmed June 9; Adventure Works ready to sign</li>
<li><b>Adatum Deal Room:</b> January notes resurfaced; competitive slides uploaded; post-meeting debrief with 70% close confidence</li>
<li>Key decisions: don&#8217;t commit GA date externally (later resolved), food manufacturing reference needed</li>
</ul>

<div class="talking-point">
&#8220;Copilot reads Teams channels too &#8212; not just my 1:1 chats. The team has been coordinating across channels all week, and I get a complete picture without scrolling through message threads.&#8221;
</div>

<hr>

<h2>Key Messages</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>#</th><th>Message</th></tr>
<tr><td>1</td><td><b>One interface, all your data</b> &#8212; emails, chats, channels, files, calendar, and CRM in one prompt</td></tr>
<tr><td>2</td><td><b>No app switching</b> &#8212; you don&#8217;t open Outlook, then Teams, then Dynamics, then Excel, then Word</td></tr>
<tr><td>3</td><td><b>Grounded in YOUR data</b> &#8212; these aren&#8217;t generic answers, they&#8217;re from your actual conversations and documents</td></tr>
<tr><td>4</td><td><b>From insight to action</b> &#8212; catch up, prep, research, analyze, and draft without leaving Copilot</td></tr>
<tr><td>5</td><td><b>Reads your documents</b> &#8212; Copilot can read and analyze Word, Excel, and PowerPoint files from OneDrive and SharePoint</td></tr>
<tr><td>6</td><td><b>Custom skills</b> &#8212; create reusable workflows for tasks you do repeatedly (deal reviews, status reports)</td></tr>
<tr><td>7</td><td><b>Prioritization</b> &#8212; Copilot identifies what&#8217;s urgent, what&#8217;s time-sensitive, and what needs your attention</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>Demo Flow Options</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Format</th><th>Duration</th><th>Prompts</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Full flow</b></td><td>~20 min</td><td>All 12 prompts</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Core demo</b></td><td>~12 min</td><td>1, 2, 5, 6, 7, 10 (catch up &#8594; deal &#8594; launch &#8594; draft &#8594; docs &#8594; triage)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Quick hit</b></td><td>~5 min</td><td>1, 2, 6 (catch up &#8594; deal deep dive &#8594; draft)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Sales-focused</b></td><td>~10 min</td><td>1, 2, 3, 7, 9 (catch up &#8594; deal &#8594; prep &#8594; docs &#8594; competitive)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Productivity-focused</b></td><td>~10 min</td><td>1, 7, 8, 10, 11 (catch up &#8594; Excel &#8594; PPT &#8594; triage &#8594; skills)</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>Pre-Demo Checklist</h2>

<ul class="checklist">
<li>Run <code>.\Load-DemoData.ps1</code></li>
<li>Verify emails visible in Outlook (26 emails &#8212; Adatum, ProLine X, escalations, status updates)</li>
<li>Verify calendar (Thursday: Adatum Corp at 10 AM, Launch Kickoff at 1 PM)</li>
<li>Verify D365 records (Accounts: Adatum Corp, Contoso Manufacturing, Tailspin Industries)</li>
<li>Verify OneDrive files (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx files appear correctly)</li>
<li>Verify Teams channels (ProLine X Launch, Adatum Deal Room, General)</li>
<li>Verify Cowork skills deployed (Documents/Cowork/skills/ in OneDrive)</li>
<li>Verify SharePoint site (ApexSalesTeam with shared docs)</li>
<li>Open Copilot Chat (microsoft365.com/chat or Teams Copilot app)</li>
<li>Close all non-demo browser tabs</li>
<li>Set calendar view to week of April 27, 2026</li>
</ul>

<h2>Reset Between Demos</h2>

<pre>.\Reset-DemoData.ps1        # clean everything
.\Load-DemoData.ps1          # reload fresh</pre>

</body>
</html>